1 A BILL for an Act to amend and reenact section 11-19.1-06 of the North Dakota Century Code,
2 relating to individuals authorized to act in the absence of a coroner.
3 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
4 SECTION 1. AMENDMENT. Section 11-19.1-06 of the North Dakota Century Code is
5 amended and reenacted as follows:
6 11-19.1-06. Individuals authorized to act in absence of coroner.
7 In those counties in which a coroner does not reside or is not available, the duties of a
8 coroner must be performed by the sheriff, the state highway patrol, or any special agent of the
9 bureau of criminal investigation. The sheriff, the state highway patrol, or special agent shall call
10 upon the nearesta coroner or deputy coroner from an adjacentanother county to investigate the
11 medical cause of death of all coroner cases within saidthe county. In those situations in which,
12 because of distance or adverse conditions, a coroner is not available, the sheriff, the state
13 highway patrol, or special agent shall request the state forensic examiner or the forensic
14 examiner's designee to investigate and certify as to the medical cause of death.
